+<!DOCTYPE html>
+<html lang="en">
+<head>
+    <meta charset="UTF-8">
+    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
+    <title>SCC Home</title>
+    <style>
+        :root {
+            color-scheme: light;
+            --bg: #f4f6f8;
+            --panel: #ffffff;
+            --text: #18212b;
+            --muted: #5f6b76;
+            --accent: #0f766e;
+            --accent-soft: #d9f3ef;
+            --border: #d7dee5;
+        }
+
+        * {
+            box-sizing: border-box;
+        }
+
+        body {
+            margin: 0;
+            font-family: "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
+            background: linear-gradient(180deg, #eef4f7 0%, #f9fbfc 100%);
+            color: var(--text);
+        }
+
+        main {
+            max-width: 920px;
+            margin: 0 auto;
+            padding: 48px 20px 80px;
+        }
+
+        .hero {
+            background: var(--panel);
+            border: 1px solid var(--border);
+            border-radius: 20px;
+            padding: 32px;
+            box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(24, 33, 43, 0.08);
+        }
+
+        .eyebrow {
+            display: inline-block;
+            margin-bottom: 12px;
+            padding: 6px 10px;
+            border-radius: 999px;
+            background: var(--accent-soft);
+            color: var(--accent);
+            font-size: 12px;
+            font-weight: 700;
+            letter-spacing: 0.08em;
+            text-transform: uppercase;
+        }
+
+        h1 {
+            margin: 0 0 12px;
+            font-size: 42px;
+            line-height: 1.1;
+        }
+
+        p {
+            margin: 0;
+            line-height: 1.6;
+        }
+
+        .lead {
+            max-width: 700px;
+            color: var(--muted);
+            font-size: 18px;
+        }
+
+        .grid {
+            display: grid;
+            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
+            gap: 16px;
+            margin-top: 28px;
+        }
+
+        .card {
+            background: #fbfcfd;
+            border: 1px solid var(--border);
+            border-radius: 16px;
+            padding: 18px;
+        }
+
+        .card h2 {
+            margin: 0 0 8px;
+            font-size: 18px;
+        }
+
+        .links {
+            display: flex;
+            flex-wrap: wrap;
+            gap: 12px;
+            margin-top: 28px;
+        }
+
+        a {
+            color: inherit;
+        }
+
+        .button {
+            display: inline-block;
+            padding: 12px 16px;
+            border-radius: 12px;
+            text-decoration: none;
+            font-weight: 600;
+            border: 1px solid var(--border);
+            background: white;
+        }
+
+        .button.primary {
+            background: var(--accent);
+            border-color: var(--accent);
+            color: white;
+        }
+
+        .section {
+            margin-top: 20px;
+            color: var(--muted);
+        }
+    </style>
+</head>
+<body>
+    <main>
+        <section class="hero">
+            <span class="eyebrow">SCC Medical App</span>
+            <h1>Home Page Starter</h1>
+            <p class="lead">
+                This is a working placeholder home page for your Django project. It is intentionally small,
+                so you can decide tomorrow whether this should stay a light dashboard, become a family
+                overview page, or just point people toward the REST API and admin tools.
+            </p>
+
+            <div class="grid">
+                <article class="card">
+                    <h2>Accounts</h2>
+                    <p>Authentication is working through django-allauth.</p>
+                </article>
+                <article class="card">
+                    <h2>Complaints</h2>
+                    <p>The app scaffold exists and is ready for models, serializers, and views.</p>
+                </article>
+                <article class="card">
+                    <h2>REST Direction</h2>
+                    <p>This project can stay API-first while still keeping a simple internal HTML dashboard.</p>
+                </article>
+            </div>
+
+            <div class="links">
+                <a class="button primary" href="/admin/">Open Admin</a>
+                <a class="button" href="/accounts/logout/">Logout</a>
+            </div>
+
+            <p class="section">
+                Tomorrow you can replace this with a real dashboard, or keep it as a small navigation page
+                while the main work happens in REST endpoints.
+            </p>
+        </section>
+    </main>
+</body>
+</html>
*** End Patch

